Paper: hep-th/9804071

Date: 1998-04-09

Title: Is the multiplicative anomaly dependent on the regularization ?

Authors: Emilio Elizalde, Antonio Filippi, Luciano Vanzo and Sergio Zerbini

Comments: 4 pages, LaTex

In a recent work, T.S. Evans has claimed that the multiplicative anomalyassociated with the zeta-function regularization of functional determinants isregularization dependent. We show that, if one makes use of consistentdefinitions, this is not the case and clarify some points in Evans' argument.